{"narrativeText":"After bidding farewell to Calmund, you make your way out of the village, the morning sun casting long shadows over the cobbled path. The locals nod respectfully as you pass, aware of your noble intent. As you reach the outskirts, the landscape shifts from farmland to untamed wilderness.

The woods lie ahead, an enigmatic labyrinth of trees and undergrowth where the air is thick with the scent of pine and the rustle of unseen creatures. This is where your hunt begins, looking for signs of disturbances that might lead you towards the lurking threats.

